<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q36_v10" title="Q36_v10" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float"><qti-default-value><qti-value>0</qti-value></qti-default-value></qti-outcome-declaration><qti-item-body>
    <p>
      En el plano cartesiano, la recta r está dada por la ecuación 
      <m:math>
        <m:mrow>
          <m:mi>x</m:mi>
          <m:mo>+</m:mo>
          <m:mi>y</m:mi>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:mn>5</m:mn>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>
      y la recta s por la ecuación 
      <m:math>
        <m:mrow>
          <m:mn>2</m:mn>
          <m:mi>x</m:mi>
          <m:mo>−</m:mo>
          <m:mi>y</m:mi>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:mn>1</m:mn>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>.
      ¿En qué punto (x, y) se intersectan las rectas r y s?
    </p>
    <div>
      <m:math>
        <m:mrow>
          <m:mo>{</m:mo>
          <m:mtable>
            <m:mtr>
              <m:mtd>
                <m:mi>r</m:mi>
                <m:mo>:</m:mo>
                <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>5</m:mn>
              </m:mtd>
            </m:mtr>
            <m:mtr>
              <m:mtd>
                <m:mi>s</m:mi>
                <m:mo>:</m:mo>
                <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
              </m:mtd>
            </m:mtr>
          </m:mtable>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>
    </div>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">(3, 2)<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Al reemplazar x = 3 e y = 2 en las ecuaciones, en r se cumple 3 + 2 = 5, pero en s se obtiene 2·3 − 2 = 4, y 4 ≠ 1. Por lo tanto, (3, 2) no pertenece a ambas rectas.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">(2, 3)<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Al reemplazar x = 2 e y = 3, en r se obtiene 2 + 3 = 5 y en s se obtiene 2·2 − 3 = 1. Como el punto satisface las dos ecuaciones al mismo tiempo, allí se intersectan las rectas.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">(1, 1)<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Al reemplazar x = 1 e y = 1 en r, se obtiene 1 + 1 = 2, y 2 ≠ 5. Además, en s se obtiene 2·1 − 1 = 1, que sí cumple solo la segunda ecuación. Por lo tanto, (1, 1) no es punto de intersección.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">(6, −1)<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Al reemplazar x = 6 e y = −1, en r se obtiene 6 + (−1) = 5, pero en s se obtiene 2·6 − (−1) = 13, y 13 ≠ 1. Por lo tanto, (6, −1) no satisface ambas ecuaciones.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso por sistema de ecuaciones</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Escribir el sistema</strong></p>
            <p>Las rectas se intersectan en el punto que satisface simultáneamente:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mo>{</m:mo>
                  <m:mtable>
                    <m:mtr>
                      <m:mtd>
                        <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                        <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                        <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                        <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                        <m:mn>5</m:mn>
                      </m:mtd>
                    </m:mtr>
                    <m:mtr>
                      <m:mtd>
                        <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                        <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                        <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                        <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                        <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                        <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                      </m:mtd>
                    </m:mtr>
                  </m:mtable>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Sumar las dos ecuaciones</strong></p>
            <p>Si sumamos miembro a miembro, <m:math><m:mrow><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math> y <m:math><m:mrow><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math> se eliminan:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>5</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>6</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Reemplazar el valor de x</strong></p>
            <p>Usamos <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> en la ecuación <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>5</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>5</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Verificar en la segunda ecuación</strong></p>
            <p>Comprobamos en <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>4</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>La igualdad se cumple.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>El punto de intersección de las rectas es <strong>(2, 3)</strong>, que corresponde a la alternativa <strong>B</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>